PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1779451869
OL,3,CChancellor's 'Great British Summer
OL,4,CSaving' is more modest than it sounds
OL,6,FThe help with food inflation is very
OL,7,Fmodest. The Food and Drink Federation
OL,8,Fcalculates that lifting tariffs on
OL,9,Ffood and drink imports will knock just
OL,10,F10 pence off the weekly shop - even if
OL,11,Fsupermarkets pass the savings on in
OL,12,Ffull.
OL,14,FChancellor Rachel Reeves has also
OL,15,Fresisted pressure to further subsidise
OL,16,Fenergy bills, which are set to rise in
OL,17,FJuly by #200.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1779451869
OL,3,CChancellor's 'Great British Summer
OL,4,CSaving' is more modest than it sounds
OL,6,FQuite right too, says the Resolution
OL,7,FFoundation. The think tank exists to
OL,8,Fchampion the fortunes of those in low
OL,9,Fand middle-income households.
OL,11,FIt points out that taxpayers' money
OL,12,Fwas sprayed around during the last
OL,13,Fenergy crisis in ways that, in some
OL,14,Fcases, benefited those who could have
OL,15,Fgot by without support. It thinks
OL,16,FReeves was right to hold back for now.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
